OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,FThe regulator wants social media firms
OL,7,Fto use photo ID and change algorithms
OL,8,Fto prevent children seeing harmful
OL,9,Fcontent
OL,11,Fplatforms must take action to stop
OL,12,Ftheir algorithms recommending harmful
OL,13,Fcontent to children, and put robust
OL,14,Fage-checking measures in place to
OL,15,Fprotect them, Ofcom has said.
OL,17,FEsther Ghey, the mother of murdered
OL,18,Fteenager , has been campaigning for an
OL,19,Fage limit on smartphone usage and
OL,20,Ftighter controls on access to social
OL,21,Fmedia.
