OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,FShe said that the regulator's draft
OL,7,Fproposals are a step in the right
OL,8,Fdirection but that they need to be
OL,9,F"less ambiguous", when speaking to
OL,10,FGood Morning Britain.
OL,12,FThe regulator has published its draft
OL,13,Fchildren's safety codes of practice,
OL,14,Fwhich set out how it expects online
OL,15,Fservices to meet their new legal
OL,16,Fresponsibilities to protect children
OL,17,Fonline under the Online Safety Act.
