OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,FThe online safety laws require sites
OL,7,Fwhich can be accessed by children to
OL,8,Fassess and take action to reduce the
OL,9,Frisks their platform poses to them.
OL,10,FThose found to be in breach of the
OL,11,Fcode could be hit with large fines.
OL,13,Fis the new regulator for the sector,
OL,14,Fand has published a range of draft
OL,15,Fcodes of practice in recent months.
OL,16,FThe new rules are set to come into
OL,17,Ffull force towards the end of this
OL,18,Fyear.
