OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,FCodes will expect services to carry
OL,7,Fout robust age verification processes
OL,8,Fto stop children accessing harmful
OL,9,Fmaterial. They will also ensure any
OL,10,Frecommendation algorithms ` such as 's
OL,11,F"For You" page ` do not serve
OL,12,Fdangerous or potentially harmful
OL,13,Fcontent to children.
OL,15,FPlatforms which can be accessed by
OL,16,Fchildren and have a higher risk of
OL,17,Fharmful content appearing must make
OL,18,Fsure their algorithms filter out the
OL,19,Fmost harmful content from children's
OL,20,Ffeeds.
