OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,FChild online safety campaigner Ian
OL,7,FRussell, the father of 14-year-old
OL,8,FMolly Russell who took her own life in
OL,9,FNovember 2017 after viewing harmful
OL,10,Fmaterial on social media, also said
OL,11,Fmore still needed to be done to
OL,12,Fprotect young people from online harms.
OL,14,FIn his role as chair of online safety
OL,15,Fcharity, the Molly Rose Foundation, Mr
OL,16,FRussell said: "Ofcom's task was to
OL,17,Fseize the moment and propose bold and
OL,18,Fdecisive measures that can protect
OL,19,Fchildren from widespread but
OL,20,Finherently preventable harm.
OL,26,@xD@OOU
