OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,F"That's why it's hugely important that
OL,7,Fthe next prime minister commits to
OL,8,Ffinish the job to and strengthen the
OL,9,FOnline Safety Act to give children and
OL,10,Ffamilies the protection they deserve."
OL,12,FOfcom chief executive, Dame Melanie
OL,13,FDawes, said: "We want children to
OL,14,Fenjoy life online. But, for too long,
OL,15,Ftheir experiences have been blighted
OL,16,Fby seriously harmful content which
OL,17,Fthey can't avoid or control.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@fO]uD@NOU
