OL,3,CEsther Ghey: Ofcom online safety rules
OL,4,Cneed to be 'less ambiguous'
OL,6,F"In line with new online safety laws,
OL,7,Four proposed Codes firmly place the
OL,8,Fresponsibility for keeping children
OL,9,Fsafer on tech firms.
OL,11,F"Our measures, which go way beyond
OL,12,Fcurrent industry standards, will
OL,13,Fdeliver a step-change in online safety
OL,14,Ffor children in the UK. Once they are
OL,15,Fin force we won't hesitate to use our
OL,16,Ffull range of enforcement powers to
OL,17,Fhold platforms to account."
